    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "How to Read This Page",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### How to read this page\\n- `Current decision` panels use the latest minute in the focus window.\\n- `Forecast` shows `+5m` to `+30m` from that latest minute.\\n- `Historical` charts show hourly context across the focus window.\\n- `Runtime alert log` shows only alerts generated in this session; it does not rebuild historical alert history.\\n- Dashboard refresh is fixed at `30m`.\\n- `external` mode is optional narrative polish; `local` mode remains authoritative for ranking, risk, forecast, and business impact.\\n- In `external` mode, page loads and each refresh cycle can trigger repeated AI-backed narrative requests because multiple panels query `/decision/focus`."
      }
